{"id": "EUVD-2024-51897", "enisaUuid": "7dd3de35-8c39-3c92-ac21-c41419669e4b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu/tegra241-cmdqv: Fix alignment failure at max_n_shift\n\nWhen configuring a kernel with PAGE_SIZE=4KB, depending on its setting of\nCONFIG_CMA_ALIGNMENT, VCMDQ_LOG2SIZE_MAX=19 could fail the alignment test\nand trigger a WARN_ON:\n    WARNING: at drivers/iommu/arm/arm-smmu-v3/arm-smmu-v3.c:3646\n    Call trace:\n     arm_smmu_init_one_queue+0x15c/0x210\n     tegra241_cmdqv_init_structures+0x114/0x338\n     arm_smmu_device_probe+0xb48/0x1d90\n\nFix it by capping max_n_shift to CMDQ_MAX_SZ_SHIFT as SMMUv3 CMDQ does.", "datePublished": "2024-12-27T13:50:14", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:07", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/85a1d70b86dbcb84a68e7e4942a5181276945988", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a3799717b881aa0f4e722afb70e7b8ba84ae4f36", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53225"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53225"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "05131879-2f54-3bf4-94dd-9fea5c319d69", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5c0de189-f906-321d-8a29-61fbe9658ecd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "918eb5c856f6ce4cf93b4b38e4b5e156905c5943 <a3799717b881aa0f4e722afb70e7b8ba84ae4f36"}, {"id": "7cbe1aad-596f-36c8-bcfb-7df2233bb4e5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.2"}, {"id": "b093c06e-aa86-3129-b5a4-92935992de8a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "d43bfe9a-ab2a-3c14-a432-6f9d9d1aee04", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12"}, {"id": "e6107099-b4c4-32a1-9ad4-6945e1474bae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "918eb5c856f6ce4cf93b4b38e4b5e156905c5943 <85a1d70b86dbcb84a68e7e4942a5181276945988"}], "enisa